<UniformSettings>
  <!--DefaultUniform: Supports arbitrary number of DefaultUniforms that are used to populate Military Uniform UI
        Name: Name of uniform
        HeadItemID: ID of item in head slot.  Must be a valid item that can be equipped
        BodyItemID: ID of item in body slot.  Must be a valid item that can be equipped
        ArmItemID: ID of item in arm slot.  Must be a valid item that can be equipped
        LegItemID: ID of item in leg slot.  Must be a valid item that can be equipped
        GloveItemID: ID of item in glove slot.  Must be a valid item that can be equipped
        FootItemID: ID of item in foot slot.  Must be a valid item that can be equipped
        LeftHandItemID: ID of item in left hand slot.  Must be a valid item that can be equipped
        RightHandItemID: ID of item in right hand slot.  Must be a valid item that can be equipped
  -->
  <!--MaterialGroup: Materials allowed for the listed item IDs.  Items in multiple groups have their materials ordered in the order of these groups. Really only used for when ITEMID_ANY is used
        OrderedMaterialID: Order that materials are prioritized when any material is selected in the uniform. ie If Helmet is selected and no material specific gnomes will first look for Steel Helmets then Iron, etc
        ItemID: ID of item that allows for materials in this group
  -->
  <!--Weapons: Populates Left and Right Hand in Military Uniform UI
        ItemID: ID of item
  -->
  <!--Shield: Items listed here are considered Shields for Military Perks
        ItemID: ID of item
  -->
  <!--Armor: Populates armor slots in Military Uniform UI based on EquipSlot defined in Items
        ItemID: ID of item
  -->
  <!--Any1HWeapon: Items to consider when ITEMID_ANY is selected for a hand.  Supports an aribitrary number of Any1HWeapons.
                   Items are prioritized first by the order each set listed here followed by highest skill for a given item within each set.
                   Ex. Gnomes will first look for Sword, HandAxe, Hammer, Pistol and if none are found then look for StoneSword, StoneHandAxe, StoneHammer.  If that gnome's highest weapon skill is Sword then he will prioritize swords, etc.
  -->
  <!--Any2HWeapon: Items to consider when ITEMID_ANY2H is selected for hands.  Supports an aribitrary number of Any2HWeapons.
                   Items are prioritized first by the order each set listed here followed by highest skill for a given item within each set.
  -->
